Security for Omnistudio Data Mappers and Integration Procedures

You can control access to Data Mappers and Integration Procedures using settings that reference Sharing Settings and Sharing Sets or Profiles and Permission Sets.

Beginning with the Winter '20 Salesforce release, Guest Users cannot access any records by default. Criteria-based Sharing Rules grant them read-only access.

Vlocity allows guest users to create and update the records to which Sharing Rules grant access.

Prior to the Summer '19 release, you might have used Salesforce Sharing Settings to secure access to Data Mappers and Integration Procedures.

Beginning with Summer '19, you can allow access based on Custom Permissions enabled in a user's Salesforce Profiles or Permission Sets.

To enforce field-level security in the data that Data Mappers access, go to the Data Mapper's Options tab and select Check Field Level Security.

A user's access includes more than the ability to run it directly. Access also applies if an application they are using calls the Data Mapper or Integration Procedure.

Configure Omnistudio Data Mapper and Integration Procedure Security Settings in Setup.

Implement the VlocityRequiredPermissionCheck Class manually because Salesforce handles classes in managed and unmanaged packages differently.

The DefaultRequiredPermission setting works properly only when this class is implemented outside of the Vlocity managed package.
title: Omnistudio Data Mapper and Integration Procedure Security
